} is a vector of random shocks. Our largest model allows for a lag order of N = 4; coefficients on higher lags are not statistically significant. The estimated parameters in this model are reported in the online appendix. Many individual parameters are statistically insignificant, and such a large model is unlikely to represent the data generating process accurately. For this reason, we also fit a restricted model in which the number of parameters is reduced using the algorithm of Krolzig & Hendry (2001). The results presented below are based on the restricted model, fitted using a Seemingly Unrelated Regressions (SUR) estimator that allows for correlations across the four error terms. The online appendix includes Maximum Likelihood estimates of the parameters, which are very similar to the SUR estimates.
